textListener`, making this more complicated than expected.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test coverage strategies**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I can cover Method#getMethod by invoking `Context.addContextListener` with a listener class that matches the target name exactly through a custom classloader without any shadowing on the main classpath. The instructions note that I can catch unsupported features for dynamic class loading, but using a fake class in a library package isn't ideal. Instead, I could potentially modify `Main.class` bytes, but that feels like a tricky workaround. Creating an instance of `Main` and using `java.lang.reflect.Proxy` doesn't seem like a viable option either.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qdEQbqh2Wp5co9ComE1K6rK3|fc_05344570d9b7e77b016a274bde38c48196a62d8fb9b92d1203", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"void addListener|interface Listener\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/main/extracted/rhino1_7R5/src/org/mozilla/javascript/ContextFactory.java -n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1345, "output": 1038, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29007, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780960189417, "responseId": "resp_05344570d9b7e77b016a274bbe1aa081968e71638fec265851"}}
