[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Assessing test coverage issues**\n\nI'm thinking about making a defensible ContextTest for the supported part, but the remaining call sites may be locked behind a legacy check. It seems like the idea of “improving test coverage” isn’t entirely accurate. Now, there’s also a concern about how dynamic-access class coverage is reported. If we use `Context.addContextListener((ContextListener) new Main(\"...\"))`, we might run into some tricky issues with ClassCastException and generics, but I'm unsure if there's a feasible workaround. It feels like there’s a bug in `addContextListener`, making this more complicated than expected.\n\n**Evaluating test coverage strategies**\n\nI'm considering whether I can cover Method#getMethod by invoking `Context.addContextListener` with a listener class that matches the target name exactly through a custom classloader without any shadowing on the main classpath. The instructions note that I can catch unsupported features for dynamic class loading, but using a fake class in a library package isn't ideal. Instead, I could potentially modify `Main.class` bytes, but that feels like a tricky workaround. Creating an instance of `Main` and using `java.lang.reflect.Proxy` doesn't seem like a viable option either.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05344570d9b7e77b016a274bbf46e48196a52500ed292a06c4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ0ve_5ia0c9wjO1-SElNgVXYcHmZw7kD_WpI4_eRonhIRYSPhRjI07UknIAmglgIsmB6QQl7Gc7BLExVlZS0QgvPc8vNsZpJfnLZldyz53mDQT1hHRX-8gSo0C5hc7rFZLjb6D9xdqBLHXfz3kggLzuRq0PpUe9MWoE-YcOcHIDEdBdCC46vT4Pc2BS-yti0J59LqONIkYPPET6rBDA6fdqoCTNRo0ka3MLwTKmjXpM1XE9Fpps-aIvGroaRfB7x_VGsYpgtgIO1JGZ0aogdbnV3ukS9BK6CW6ONB9cLw6zWd0hdaF2rEtr_j_FIOXX3lACz3r3P0GL8n4w4evRQqxiz5eJkQt-9BHyQOzf3hM1u2rvkNLyOh_-2Xcx73_Exa9w_X1szDzET2RFJkZaa4A3KrYm8YclfSLqVskO6BFhZPXidRkolnnNMQhNLnEZBGmU_kAgKwsWWdUQ9-qrX9tyQqNW